all, Orleans County New York, where he died Christmas Day 1858 at age seventy. He was buried at Greenwood Cemetery Kendall, far from the Hooker-line Connecticut center."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Presumed daughter's line reconverged Hooker branches","body":"Through Laura E. Hooker Shader — Myron's presumed daughter by first wife Sally Brooks — the line runs forward to Caroline E. Shader who married Thomas Harvey Hooker, descendant of Myron's half-brother Thomas Gould Hooker. That third-cousin marriage between two branches of Captain Thomas Hooker's descendants reconverged a line that had split four generations earlier. Their child Charles Theodore Hooker qualifies as double Hooker ancestry."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Greenwood Cemetery, Kendall, Orleans County NY (per WikiTree). Cemetery not yet built as separate CEM entry."},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"myron-hooker-1788"},"HD3260":{"id":"HD3260","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":8},"bio":{"first_name":"Laura","middle_name":"Electa","last_name":"Shader","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":["Shader"],"extra_names":"Not in EH 1272 — almost certainly an EH omission. Per WikiTree (which lists her as Betsy Bacon's daughter, likely confused with Sally Brooks who was the biological mother).","gender":"female","display_name":"Laura Electa Hooker Shader","bio_blurb":"Vermont-born Hooker daughter who lived to ninety-three"},"birth":{"year":1818,"state":"Vermont","country":"United States","historical_notes":"Per WikiTree: b.1818 Vermont — making her older than her EH-listed siblings Myron Smith (1820) and Thomas Cullen (1822). Likely Myron Hooker + Sally Brooks first child; EH 1272 omitted her, possibly because she had no Hooker-surname descendants to track."},"death":{"year":1911,"month":11,"day":7,"city":"Shelton","county":"Fairfield County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H01272","mother_id":"X02278","father_research_notes":"Myron Hooker (H01272)","mother_research_notes":"Per Findagrave: Betsey Bacon Hooker (X02278). EARLIER hypothesis was Sally Brooks (X02277) based on timing logic (Laura b.1818, Sally Brooks's children Myron Smith b.1820 and Thomas Cullen b.1822). Findagrave likely correct that Betsey is the BIOLOGICAL mother — meaning Betsey may have been Myron's first wife, OR Laura was Betsey's daughter from her earlier Bacon marriage who took Hooker surname after her mother remarried Myron. EH 1272 omitted Laura entirely. UNRESOLVED — going with Findagrave per primary memorial source."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02280","location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["X02269","HD3269","HD3274"]}],"tags":["extraordinary_longevity","new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"WikiTree: Laura E. (Hooker) Shader","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Casteel-170"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"character","header":"She buried the genealogist’s mistake by outliving everyone","body":"Born in frontier Vermont in 1818, she lived to ninety-three — long enough to see the railroad, the telegraph, the Civil War, and electric light reach the country towns of her girlhood. One of her daughters, Violetta, raised thirteen children of her own."}],"cross_connections":[{"related_person_id":"H02424","relationship":"first_cousin_cousin_marriage_convergence","evidence":"Laura's father Myron Hooker and Thomas Edwin's father Thomas Gould were half-brothers via Capt. Thomas 